                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On the evening of November 7, 1951, President Truman delivered a radio and
                    television report to the American people on international arms reduction, with
                    particular reference to the United States United Kingdom-France declaration
                    released in Paris earlier in the day. For text of the tripartite declaration,
                    see telegram <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 72, <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>. For text of the President’s address, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States: Harry S. Truman,
                        1951</hi>, pages 623–627, or Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, November 19, 1951, pages 799–803.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
